  To give you an idea what to build, here's my curret racing and freestyle setups. The list isn't complete, as I usually have 2-3 spares and some variants for freestyle with different motors etc. Unless specifically stated, all rigs use TBS Unify HV or Unify Race VTXes.

  ### Rotorama Split Samurai  ###

  <p class="image full">
    <img src="/images/hangar/samuraisplit.jpg"/>
  </p>
  
  I have fallen in love with the new category of superlight 5" frames. This one sports the Runcam Split Camera, so it's a bit laggier for proper racing, but does 1080P/60 HD recording at 226g. Not only does the size allow it to stop on a dime and just feels ridiculous for cornering, it can do proper races on a 850mah battery and does really well even on lousy 1300. The typical powerhorse 5" neeeds the most dense and fresh packs to sustain the full throttle for more than a second. This guy can scream through the whole pack.

