  ### Red20RC BDX Racer ###

  <p class="image full">
    <img src="/images/hangar/bdxr.jpg"/>
  </p>
    
  I've got 4 BDX Racer quads suitable for both racing and freestyle. As the weight is becoming an issue with non-unibody frames, I'm slowly phasing out the BDXR from racing and keeping them as my day to day bashers/freestyle quads.
  
  I've finally bought the Connex Prosight HD system and one of the BDXRs is equipped with that. Overall the BDXR is still light enough to be competititve and is extremely durable. Been through some very rough crashes. The early designs had a weakness in the camera housing, but that has since been resolved.

